        "alert_help_advanced_title": "Advanced",
        "alert_help_autocut": "An Autocut is a text file stored on iCloud Drive or Dropbox that instructs Autocuts to run a shortcut automatically while you use your iOS device during the day. Each Autocut has the following properties:\n\n• shortcut: the shortcut to run.\n\n• date: the date and time that an Autocut can first be run.\n\n• expires: the amount of time in minutes after the scheduled date that an Autocut can still be run. Shortcuts of expired Autocuts will not run. Autocuts can also be set to never expire.\n\n• device: the name of the iOS device that can run this Autocut. Leave blank to run the Autocut on any device. \n\n• activate: set to true to open the Shortcuts app before running the Autocut's shortcut. Used for those shortcuts that do not run properly in the background.\n\n• input: text input that will be sent to an Autocut's shortcut when run.",
        "alert_help_autocut_title": "What is an Autocut?",
        "alert_help_creating": "Autocuts can be created in a number of ways. Any shortcut or application that can write to the Shortcuts folder on iCloud Drive or a Dropbox folder can create an Autocut.\n\nSome examples include:\n\n• Autocuts Admin: the shortcut you are using now features an assistant that walks tou step-by-step in creating an Autocut.\n\n• API: Send the Autocuts Admin a specially-formatted dictionary to create and schedule Autocuts from a third-party shortcut.\n\n• IFTTT or Zapier: any trigger can write an Autocut text file to an Autocuts Dropbox source folder.",

Make sure to add this folder path as a source if you want Autocuts on this device to process them.\n\n• Dropbox: A folder on Dropbox where to store your Autocut files. Make sure to add this folder path as a source if you want Autocuts on this device to process them.\n\n• IFTTT: Requires a Maker Webhooks Event name and API key to send a webhook to IFTTT which should create an Autocut file on Dropbox.\n\n• Zapier: Requires catch hook URL to send an Autocut to Zapier. var sourcePath = "￼";
var sourceType = "￼";

// We sort by name and active status
let filter = [￼];

if ( filter.length &gt; 0 ) {
	var filteredAutocuts = autocutsUnsorted.filter( function( obj ) {
		for ( var i = 0; i &lt; filter.length; i++ ) {
			if ( typeof obj["tags"] !== "undefined" &amp;&amp; obj["tags"].toLowerCase().split("\n").indexOf( filter[i].toLowerCase() ) != -1 ) {
				return true;
			}
		}
	});
} else {
	var filteredAutocuts = autocutsUnsorted;
}

filteredAutocuts = filteredAutocuts.sort( function(a, b) {
	if ( a.active &gt; b.active ) {
		return -1;
	} else if ( a.active &lt; b.active ) {
		return 1;
	} else if ( a.active == b.active ) {
		if ( a.name &lt; b.name ) {
			return -1;
		} else if ( a.name &gt; b.name ) {
			return 1;
		}
		return 0;
	}
});


// Return vCards

var result = [];
var len = filteredAutocuts.length;

for( var i = 0; i &lt; len; i++ ) {
	var autocut = filteredAutocuts[i];
	var description = [];
	
		// Name
	
	if ( typeof autocut.name === "undefined" || autocut.name == "" ) {
		var name = autocut.shortcut;	
	} else {
		var name = autocut.name;
	}
	
		// File path
	
	var path = sourcePath + "/" + autocut.fileName + "." + autocut.fileExtension;
	
		// Icon
		
	if ( typeof autocut.active != "undefined" &amp;&amp; autocut.active == true ) {
		var icon = "";
	} else {
		var icon = "";
	}
		
		// Date
	/*	
	if ( typeof autocut.date !== "undefined" || autocut.date == "" ) {
		var date = new Date();	
	} else {
		var date = new Date ( Date.parse( autocut.date ) );
	}
	
	if ( date &gt;= new Date() ) {
		var dateFormat = new DateFormatter();
		
		dateFormat.useMediumDateStyle();
		dateFormat.useMediumTimeStyle();
		dateFormat.date( autocut.date );
		

		console.log(dateFormat.);
		
		description.push( dateFormat );
	} else {
			
	}
	*/
		
		// Repeat Interval
	
	if ( typeof autocut.interval !== "undefined" &amp;&amp; autocut.interval != 0 &amp;&amp; typeof autocut.unit !== "undefined" &amp;&amp; autocut.unit != "" ) {
		description.push( "🔄 " + autocut.interval + autocut.unit );
	}
	
		// Background
	
	if ( typeof autocut.activate !== "undefined" &amp;&amp; autocut.activate == true ) {
		description.push( "↗️" );
	}
	
		// Description
	
	if ( typeof autocut.device !== "undefined" &amp;&amp; autocut.device != "" ) {
		description.push( "📱" );
		description.push( autocut.device );
	}
	
	description = description.join(" ");
	
	var vcard = "BEGIN:VCARD\nVERSION:3.0\nN:" + name + ";\nTITLE:" + sourceType + ";\nNOTE:" + path + "\nORG:" + description + ";\nPHOTO;ENCODING=b:" + icon + "\nEND:VCARD";
	
	result.push( vcard );
}

result = result.join("\n");

document.write ( '{ "filteredAutocuts": ' + JSON.stringify( result ) + '}' );

- Evaluation Information about the shortcuts that will run
- Middle: Before running shortcuts
- End: Evaluation and running of shortcuts complete
- Interval Reminder: When the Open App runs but we're in between the interval to run Autocuts automatically. Displays a notification allowing the user to manually run Autocuts.</string>
			</dict>
